N:obsidian-cli
D:[obsidian-cli] Route Obsidian desktop automation to the right first-party surface: official Obsidian CLI for terminal/TUI commands against a running app, official obsidian:// URIs for launcher/callback handoff, and explicit route-outs for headless sync, filesystem writes, or richer plugin/API automation.
G:obsidian cli obsidian uri vault notes automation callbacks developer-tools headless route-out tui

U[8]:
  Enable and verify the official Obsidian CLI inside the desktop app
  Run one-shot commands or the interactive TUI against a running Obsidian instance
  Target a specific vault and note with vault= file= or exact path=
  Use daily search read create tags tasks diff and command-palette execution from the shell
  Use developer commands such as plugin:reload devtools dev:screenshot and eval
  Launch official obsidian:// open new daily unique search and hook-get-address flows
  Explain callback and encoding rules for URI handoff workflows
  Route headless sync raw markdown writes or richer plugin/API automation away from this skill

S[6]{n,action,details}:
  1,Classify primary surface,choose cli-command cli-tui cli-developer uri-handoff or an explicit route-out before giving commands
  2,Verify desktop runtime,use bash scripts/install.sh and confirm Settings -> General -> Command line interface is enabled
  3,Target deterministically,put vault= first and prefer exact path= when file= could be ambiguous
  4,Operate,run official CLI commands for shell-visible daily search read create tags tasks diff or command id flows
  5,Handoff,use bash scripts/open-uri.sh with official obsidian:// actions when another app or callback is involved
  6,Route out,send headless sync to Obsidian Headless and richer external automation to filesystem or plugin/API workflows instead of overclaiming CLI coverage

R[8]:
  Obsidian CLI controls the desktop app and current docs say installer version 1.12.7+ is required
  The app must be desktop-accessible and the first CLI command can launch it if closed
  vault= must come before the command when targeting a non-default vault
  Prefer exact path= over file= for agent-safe deterministic targeting
  daily and unique depend on their respective plugins being enabled
  URI values must be encoded and paneType=window is desktop-only
  Developer commands are stateful app operations and should be treated deliberately
  Headless sync publish or richer external CRUD automation are route-outs not hidden sub-modes of this skill

E[6]{type,command}:
  Verify,bash scripts/install.sh
  Search,obsidian vault="My Vault" search query="meeting notes"
  Read,obsidian vault="My Vault" read path="Projects/Roadmap.md"
  Developer,obsidian plugin:reload id=my-plugin
  URI,bash scripts/open-uri.sh 'obsidian://open?vault=my%20vault&file=my%20note'
  Route-out,Use Obsidian Headless or a plugin/API workflow when no desktop app or richer external control is required
